WEBVTT

00:00:01.229 --> 00:00:04.669
Pursuing peace can be a challenge.

00:00:04.669 --> 00:00:08.830
Because of our imperfections and the complexities of life,

00:00:08.830 --> 00:00:13.230
we have to work for peace, even under normal conditions.

00:00:13.230 --> 00:00:18.870
But pursuing peace becomes a greater challenge when it's one-sided.

00:00:18.870 --> 00:00:22.789
Difficult these arise in the family and in the congregation

00:00:22.789 --> 00:00:26.789
when one person pursues peace, but the other does not.

00:00:26.789 --> 00:00:30.390
For example, in the congregation, perhaps we have a friend

00:00:30.589 --> 00:00:33.990
who has a problem with another friend in the congregation,

00:00:33.990 --> 00:00:37.350
but does not do anything to reconcile the situation.

00:00:37.350 --> 00:00:42.829
Or in the family, a Christian mate may have difficulty pursuing peace

00:00:42.829 --> 00:00:46.869
if his or her spouse does not apply Bible principles.

00:00:46.869 --> 00:00:48.909
Well, what do we do then?

00:00:48.909 --> 00:00:54.229
Well, in those situations, the Bible account of Abigail may be helpful.

00:00:54.229 --> 00:00:58.310
And invite you to turn in your Bibles through 1 Samuel, chapter 25.

00:00:58.310 --> 00:01:02.630
And here we're introduced to Abigail and her husband, Nebel.

00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:07.150
And you notice here in verse 3, Nebel is described as harsh.

00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:12.310
In verse 25, Abigail describes him as senseless.

00:01:12.310 --> 00:01:17.430
In verse 17, his own worker describes him as worthless

00:01:17.430 --> 00:01:20.510
and says nobody can speak with him.

00:01:20.510 --> 00:01:22.870
Well, with a personality like that,

00:01:22.870 --> 00:01:27.189
it's not surprising that his name is Streets, David's young man.

00:01:27.230 --> 00:01:30.430
And now David wants revenge.

00:01:30.430 --> 00:01:35.230
How do you pursue peace in a situation like that?

00:01:35.230 --> 00:01:37.670
What does Abigail do?

00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:41.510
Well, you think about it, what she could have done.

00:01:41.510 --> 00:01:44.870
See, Abigail could have done nothing.

00:01:44.870 --> 00:01:47.230
It's not hard to imagine that she had a difficult life

00:01:47.230 --> 00:01:48.989
as well living with this man.

00:01:48.989 --> 00:01:52.069
She could have just stepped back, let David come through

00:01:52.069 --> 00:01:54.030
and do what he had in mind.

00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:56.349
Or she could have gone out to David

00:01:56.390 --> 00:01:58.109
and inflamed the situation,

00:01:58.109 --> 00:02:00.469
maybe describing what a terrible man he is

00:02:00.469 --> 00:02:03.469
and how he mistreats her as well.

00:02:03.469 --> 00:02:07.909
See, either these approaches could have made her life easier

00:02:07.909 --> 00:02:09.789
but she didn't do that.

00:02:09.789 --> 00:02:13.469
Now, Abigail could not change her husband's ways

00:02:13.469 --> 00:02:18.229
but she did what she could to diffuse an escalating conflict.

00:02:18.229 --> 00:02:21.349
In fact, notice her respectful, well chosen words.

00:02:21.349 --> 00:02:23.909
Let's go back to 1 Samuel 25

00:02:23.949 --> 00:02:29.259
and let's read verses 27 through 31.

00:02:29.259 --> 00:02:31.939
Now, let this gift that your servant girl

00:02:31.939 --> 00:02:34.539
has brought to my Lord be given to the young man

00:02:34.539 --> 00:02:36.860
who are following my Lord.

00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:40.699
Pardon please, the transgression of your servant girl.

00:02:40.699 --> 00:02:42.740
For Jehovah will without fail,

00:02:42.740 --> 00:02:45.620
make for my Lord a lasting house

00:02:45.620 --> 00:02:49.099
because my Lord is fighting the wars of Jehovah

00:02:49.099 --> 00:02:52.939
and no evil has been found in you all your days.

00:02:52.979 --> 00:02:57.740
When someone rises up to pursue you and seeks your life,

00:02:57.740 --> 00:03:00.659
the life of my Lord will be wrapped securely

00:03:00.659 --> 00:03:03.939
in the bag of life with Jehovah your God.

00:03:03.939 --> 00:03:05.699
But the lives of your enemies,

00:03:05.699 --> 00:03:08.500
he will hurl away like stones from a sling.

00:03:09.259 --> 00:03:11.180
And when Jehovah has done for my Lord

00:03:11.180 --> 00:03:13.340
all the good things he has promised

00:03:13.340 --> 00:03:16.780
and he points you as leader over Israel,

00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:20.460
you will have no remorse or regret in your heart

00:03:20.460 --> 00:03:22.819
for shedding blood without cause

00:03:22.819 --> 00:03:26.259
and for letting the hand of my Lord take revenge.

00:03:26.259 --> 00:03:30.060
When Jehovah confers good upon my Lord,

00:03:30.060 --> 00:03:33.060
remember your servant girl.

00:03:33.060 --> 00:03:35.020
And do you notice what Abigail does?

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:37.020
She comes in with the gift.

00:03:37.020 --> 00:03:38.979
She bows down to David.

00:03:38.979 --> 00:03:42.139
She takes the blame for the situation herself

00:03:42.139 --> 00:03:46.060
and she reasons with him using godly principles.

00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:51.860
Abigail's actions calm David and a verdict calamity.

00:03:52.340 --> 00:03:55.300
She pursued peace.

00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:59.099
But to do that she had to look beyond her own feelings

00:03:59.099 --> 00:04:02.180
and consider what was best for Jehovah's name.

00:04:02.180 --> 00:04:04.699
And that is not always easy to do.

00:04:04.699 --> 00:04:06.259
But what was the result?

00:04:06.259 --> 00:04:09.460
Because she sowed peace, she pursued peace,

00:04:09.460 --> 00:04:11.099
she reaped peace.

