00:08:04.550 --> 00:08:09.029
See, Amy's desire to sow peace moved her to help Lena

00:08:09.029 --> 00:08:11.709
see things from a different perspective.

00:08:11.709 --> 00:08:16.709
And as a result, the congregation benefited and reaped peace.

00:08:17.509 --> 00:08:20.990
Notice how the Apostle Paul explains this approach

00:08:20.990 --> 00:08:22.230
that we should take.

00:08:22.230 --> 00:08:26.589
If you turn to your Bibles to Romans, chapter 12 and verse 18.

00:08:27.670 --> 00:08:30.509
Romans, chapter 12 and verse 18.

00:08:31.470 --> 00:08:35.190
If possible, as far as it depends on you,

00:08:35.190 --> 00:08:37.470
be peaceable with all men.

00:08:38.470 --> 00:08:41.870
As far as it depends on you.

00:08:41.870 --> 00:08:45.029
See, our congregations, our families benefit

00:08:45.029 --> 00:08:50.029
when we sow seeds of peace before matters get out of hand.

00:08:50.190 --> 00:08:53.149
It's like seeing a small fire in our house.

00:08:53.149 --> 00:08:54.350
What do we do?

00:08:54.350 --> 00:08:56.029
Do we just ignore it?

00:08:56.029 --> 00:08:57.509
And hope it goes away?

00:08:57.509 --> 00:08:59.309
Do we fan the flames?

00:08:59.309 --> 00:09:00.389
Do we put fuel on it?

00:09:00.389 --> 00:09:01.389
No, we do something.

00:09:01.389 --> 00:09:02.149
Why?

00:09:02.149 --> 00:09:05.070
Because we know that if left unchecked,

00:09:05.070 --> 00:09:07.870
that fire could destroy our home.

00:09:08.830 --> 00:09:11.110
Well, as similar when we see problems

00:09:11.110 --> 00:09:13.669
that develop in peace being disrupted,

00:09:13.669 --> 00:09:14.509
we do the same.

00:09:14.509 --> 00:09:15.350
Why?

00:09:15.350 --> 00:09:17.750
Because we know that if we don't do something,

00:09:17.750 --> 00:09:19.990
and if it's left unchecked,

00:09:19.990 --> 00:09:24.990
that disturbance could destroy our family and the congregation.

00:09:25.830 --> 00:09:27.149
So the question is,

00:09:27.149 --> 00:09:30.750
is how do we sow seeds of peace?

00:09:30.750 --> 00:09:32.190
Well, Abigail was a good example.

00:09:32.190 --> 00:09:33.750
Did you notice what she did?

00:09:33.750 --> 00:09:37.110
Is she considered how best to approach the situation?

00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:38.789
She was proactive.

00:09:38.789 --> 00:09:41.950
She didn't just hope it would go away on its own.

00:09:41.950 --> 00:09:45.590
She used respectful, soothing speech.

00:09:45.590 --> 00:09:50.269
She was careful not to fan the flames or add fuel to it.

00:09:50.269 --> 00:09:52.789
Oh, good steps we can take.

00:09:52.789 --> 00:09:55.429
And we have other resources to help us as well.

00:09:55.429 --> 00:09:59.230
We can do research in the Bible and in our publications

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:02.909
to see how others have sowed peace in similar situations.

00:10:02.909 --> 00:10:05.669
And we can also consult with the elders.

00:10:06.870 --> 00:10:11.190
Now, we understand that this is especially a challenge

00:10:11.190 --> 00:10:16.190
if the situation is in the family as it was for Abigail.

00:10:16.190 --> 00:10:18.629
That is not easy at all.

00:10:18.629 --> 00:10:20.470
And in those situations,

00:10:20.509 --> 00:10:24.110
try to focus on your mate's good qualities,

00:10:24.110 --> 00:10:28.070
not on his or her irritating traits.

00:10:28.070 --> 00:10:31.350
But with all of this, we have to be realistic.

00:10:31.350 --> 00:10:32.990
Remember what the Apostle Paul said there

00:10:32.990 --> 00:10:35.070
is recorded in verse 18?

00:10:35.070 --> 00:10:40.070
He says, if possible, as far as it depends on you.

00:10:41.230 --> 00:10:44.110
So Paul was acknowledging that peace with others

00:10:44.110 --> 00:10:46.830
may not always be possible.

00:10:46.830 --> 00:10:48.269
So what do we do?

00:10:48.309 --> 00:10:50.629
We have to do the best that we can.

00:10:50.629 --> 00:10:53.230
And then we leave the rest in Jehovah's hands.

00:10:54.149 --> 00:10:58.669
So may we be determined to develop the practice

00:10:58.669 --> 00:11:01.350
of pursuing peace now.

